{
  "texts": [
    "A survey compared existing generation-only, retrieval-only, and RAG models (Zhang et al., 2023) but with different base models, hindering the comparison of the techniques.",
    "We study and compare in-context learning and fine-tuning as techniques to adapt LLMs for human-machine dialogues.",
    "We select Llama-2 Chat (Llama2 C) (Touvron et al., 2023) and Mistral Instruct (Mistral I) (Jiang et al., 2023) as base LLMs, and experiment in the context of four dialogue types: Open-Domain Dialogue (ODD), Knowledge-Grounded Dialogue (KGD), Task-Oriented Dialogue (TOD), and Question Answering (QA).",
    "For each technique and dialogue type, we assess the impact of grounding the generation on documents in the scenarios of retrieved knowledge (RAG) and gold knowledge.",
    "In our experiment, we have selected a dataset for each of the four dialogue types (see §A.1 for selection)."
  ]
}